name: Girl in LA
description:
My second drop is “Girl in LA”
Autism children always love stuff, material, like train, railways, airplane and else. Because they seem organized, powerful, speedy, and interesting to see. 
Now my age is 18. My parent want me to know the definition of girl. That’s why they ask me to paint “Girl in LA”. It’s about iconic girl “Marylin”  who wear white skirt show her cuteness when the skirt blown away by wind. She travel to LA with a lot of alternative airlines. 
Now I know girl is wearing skirt, they have nice attractive smile, and they have cuteness compare to boys.
